org.jmisb.api.klv.st0601

Class GenericFlagData01

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jmisb.api.klv.st0601.GenericFlagData01
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IKlvValue, INestedKlvValue, IUasDatalinkValue

    public class GenericFlagData01
extends Object
implements IUasDatalinkValue, INestedKlvValue
    Generic Flag Data (ST 0601 Item 47).

    From ST:

    Generic metadata flags.

    The Generic Data Flags are miscellaneous boolean (yes / no) aircraft and image related data settings which are individual bits in a single byte value.

    Initial versions of ST0601.13, ST0601.14, ST0601.15 and ST0601.16 inadvertently reversed the meaning of these bits. We use the original (intended) meaning as published in the updated (ST0601.13a, ST0601.14a, ST0601.15a and ST0601.16a) versions, not the interpretation published in the initial versions.

    • Constructor Detail

      • GenericFlagData01

        public GenericFlagData01(List<FlagDataKey> values)
        Create from value.

        Each of the keys that is set in the parameter list will be set (1). The meaning of set is:

        • LaserRange: Laser is on.
        • AutoTrack: Auto-track is on.
        • IR_Polarity: Black hot.
        • IcingStatus: Icing detected.
        • SlantRange: Measured.
        Parameters:
        values - the values to set on this flagged data instance.
